{"word":"ἄφρακτος","slug":"ἄφρακτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄφρακτος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φράσσω'><el>φράσσω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>unfenced, unfortified, unguarded</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἄφρ. φίλων</el> <i>by</i> friends, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <el>ἄφρ. ὅρκοις</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>not to be kept in, irrepressible</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>unguarded, off one's guard</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}